	   <tr><td colspan=2>If all things were equal between the sword-swinging classes, then yes, 2h would be the perfect solution for knight 99% of the time, but I'm gonna let you in a little secret.<br><br>We can't hit for beans.<br><br>No, really.&nbsp;&nbsp;Compared to other melee classes, our hit/miss ratio is pretty crummy.  Slow weapons= less hits.  High ratio 1h weapons make up for that in sheer seed and reasonable damage.  They're also a lot easier to train up, since they're nice and fast.  Slower, heavier 2H weapons are nice for situations where you need decent damage output without having to worry about gaining aggro, that's what I use my Protector for.  1:1 and better ratio weapons (Whether 1h or 2h) aren't ideal for situations where your guild is relying on a MT.<br><br>We can deal a decent amount of damage with our slower 2h'ers while still being able to fire off stuns and other hate-mongering spells, which is a definite plus when fighting caster NPCs in a raid situation, or we can switch to fast-swinging quick-succession 1:1 ratio 1-hand weapons and carve stuff up something fierce.  Hitting for 100+ on a &lt;=30 delay weapon works just fine for DMG output in most situations, since the 2h weaps hit for under 100 a great deal anyway.  Why wait to get the same hit? :)<br><br>If the organization or grammar sucks a bit, I'm sorry, just came off of 8 hours of binge-raiding and I'm seriously tired :)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
